{"type":"message","id":"59663930","parentId":"fd37e0fa","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:57:01.354Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_czrsyt1kx60x_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 025613\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 complete\r\n- TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement the TIC experiment on the pulse log files. Let me look at what needs to be done:\r\n\r\n1. First, I need to understand what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Then implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me check what files are available in the sandbox. I should look at:\r\n- logs/pulse_*.md files\r\n- The TIC experiment doc that was just appended\r\n\r\nSince I'm a stateless agent starting fresh, I need to:\r\n1. Check what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n3. Run the experiment\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to implement the TIC classifier. Let me create a script or document that advances this goal.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes:\r\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute\r\n- The LLM call dominates\r\n- Need to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n\r\nI should create the TIC classifier implementation. The most direct file edit would be to create a script that performs the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier on the pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs, then validates prediction accuracy. The pulse logs exist in `logs/` but the actual classifier implementation is the critical next step.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic-classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant patterns, classifies content, and measures prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MinConfidence = 70,\r\n    [int]$PredictionThreshold = 60\r\n)\r\n\r\n$logsPath = \"logs\"\r\n$resultsPath = \"research/tic-results.md\"\r\n$lastPulse = Get-Content \"state/last_pulse.txt\" -EA SilentlyContinue\r\n\r\n# Get all pulse logs sorted by time\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem \"$logsPath/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient pulse logs for TIC experiment (need 5+, found $($pulseLogs.Count))\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC Experiment: Analyzing $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content patterns from each pulse\r\n$patterns = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    # Extract key patterns: goals referenced, files modified, insights generated\r\n    $patterns += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $log.Name\r\n        Goals = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?m)^##?\\s+(.+)$') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n        Files = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?:\\.\\.\\/|\\.\\/)?([\\w\\/-]+\\.\\w+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value } | Select-Object -Unique\r\n        Insights = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)(?:insight|hypothesis|key finding|synthesis):(.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify INVARIANTS: patterns that recur across multiple pulses\r\n$invariantCandidates = @{}\r\nforeach ($p in $patterns) {\r\n    foreach ($goal in $p.Goals) {\r\n        if (-not $invariantCandidates[$goal]) { $invariantCandidates[$goal] = 0 }\r\n        $invariantCandidates[$goal]++\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$invariants = $invariantCandidates.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value -ge 2 } | Sort-Object Value -Descending\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"`nINVARIANTS (recur in 2+ pulses):\"\r\n$invariants | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  - $($_.Key) (appears in $($_.Value) pulses)\" }\r\n\r\n# Classify each pulse: invariant-heavy vs variant-heavy\r\n$classificationResults = @()\r\n$totalPulseCount = $patterns.Count\r\n\r\nforeach ($p in $patterns) {\r\n    $invariantCount = ($p.Goals | Where-Object { $invariants.Name -contains $_ }).Count\r\n    $totalCount = $p.Goals.Count + $p.Insights.Count + 1\r\n    $invariantRatio = if ($totalCount -gt 0) { ($invariantCount / $totalCount) * 100 } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    $classification = if ($invariantRatio -ge 50) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n    $classificationResults += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $p.File\r\n        Classification = $classification\r\n        InvariantRatio = [math]::Round($invariantRatio, 1)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$invariantClassified = ($classificationResults | Where-Object { $_.Classification -eq \"INVARIANT\" }).Count\r\n$classificationAccuracy = ($invariantClassified / $totalPulseCount) * 100\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"`nCLASSIFICATION RESULTS:\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Invariant: $($invariantClassified) pulses ($([math]::Round($classificationAccuracy, 1))%)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Variant:\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:56:45\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335421352}}
